@N1024:  walk the segment table back to front
@N1025:  first table entry
@N1026:         td tmp_tabx
@N1027:  second table entry
@N1030:         td tmp_taby
@N1031:  third table entry
@N1032:  end of debug hack
@N1033:  branch if most significant bit is on
@N1035:  shift AC left by one bit
@N1042:         td tmp_tabx
@N1045:         td tmp_taby
@N1052:  advance x position to the next character
@N1055:  bail out when count exhausted
@N1056:  overwritten by the table y value
@N1057:  if the character has a descender, reduce the y value
@N1060:  add the current screen y value
@N1061:  initialize vector gen with the y-coord in ACC
@N1062:  the RC uses AC to set X coord and mem address for the vector length
@N1067:  shift pointer to Upper Case table & exit
